:{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"zWPHtWShNp"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"震源激发的机械振动以地震波的形式在地球内部传播。地震波分为体波（body wave）\n和面波（surface wave）两种类型。体波是指在地球内部传播的波，而面波是指在地球表面\n附近传播的波。本节将介绍最基础的地震波理论。","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"J9DZxMh7NU"}],"key":"Ja9TrO3C9s"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"体波","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"G68X3RGMba"}],"identifier":"id","label":"体波","html_id":"id","implicit":true,"key":"IIgELwelZp"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"体波分为 P 波（P-wave）和 S 波（S-wave）两种。","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"xxH60kuQoY"}],"key":"loD3huVSW0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"从传播速度的角度看，P 波比 S 波传播速度快。因而 P 波总是最先到达观测者所在的位置，\nS 波则在 P 波后到达。因而，P 波和 S 波也分别被称为 ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"Qzrx0cau5o"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"p","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"KSnI5RpcaQ"}],"key":"oV3nt3svbP"},{"type":"text","value":"rimary wave 和 ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"fXuIsSYjXs"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"s","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"ZuPLC8UbxN"}],"key":"oJDUg8Arfh"},{"type":"text","value":"econdary wave。","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"mvuXdpPWLj"}],"key":"PUMxbakpss"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"从物理属性上来说，P 波是一种纵波（longitudinal wave），P 波在介质中传播时，介质的\n运动方向与波传播的方向相同或相反，介质交替压缩和膨胀导致介质的体积发生变化（如下图所示），\n因而 P 波也称为压缩波（com","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"vf7BV2BfsH"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"p","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"rDitWQjtR6"}],"key":"NTieLarPcb"},{"type":"text","value":"ressional wave）。S 波是一种横波（transverse wave），\nS 波在介质中传播时，介质的运动方向与波传播的方向垂直，会造成介质的剪切变形，但\n不改变介质的体积（如下图示），因而 S 波也称为剪切波（","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"Eg0tZaJMZ3"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"s","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"m33cfmywDR"}],"key":"a0LuiIpZqZ"},{"type":"text","value":"hear wave）。","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"OyrFvUiR6I"}],"key":"LSf3MR4y5q"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"事实上，地震学家首先根据波到达的先后顺序将两种波命名为 primary wave 和 secondary wave，\n并简称为 P-wave 和 S-wave，最后在进一步理解了两种地震波的物理属性后，才分别\n将其称为 com","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"yv69kXIOQJ"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"p","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"DdCPFWJps0"}],"key":"OpkIEL5LgF"},{"type":"text","value":"ressional wave 和 ","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"youS9mTIG9"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"s","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"OR3WOO0zNq"}],"key":"t0ersswGjb"},{"type":"text","value":"hear wave。","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"do76rolc6V"}],"key":"LSynMypWFH"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/seismology101/build/body-wave-propagatio-ea58998af100136e7ea79e834c3137f3.jpg","alt":"\"体波的介质运动方向以及波传播方向\"","width":"80%","align":"center","key":"RQ11oCF1YR","urlSource":"body-wave-propagation.jpg"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"体波的介质运动方向以及波传播方向。引自《","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"ETwMDanbbg"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.cambridge.org/us/academic/subjects/earth-and-environmental-science/solid-earth-geophysics/introduction-seismology-3rd-edition?format=HB&isbn=9781316635742","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Introduction to Seismology","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"lUQk8CfGYb"}],"urlSource":"https://www.cambridge.org/us/academic/subjects/earth-and-environmental-science/solid-earth-geophysics/introduction-seismology-3rd-edition?format=HB&isbn=9781316635742","key":"VljQmT83Qm"},{"type":"text","value":"》（第三版）图 3.2。","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"iTb6VtUkKH"}],"key":"Cbob0oYsF1"}],"key":"mgHap9isGY"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"jL5Q9ExQnS"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"面波","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"lin